The paper deals with the problem of approximating the minimum cut in a distributed message-passing model, which is a classic problem in distributed computing. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves graph algorithms and optimization, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The distributed message-passing model involves communication networks, which could place the paper in cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper proposes a new algorithm, which could also place it in cs.AL (Algorithms).
